    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require prominent labelling for halal and kosher certified items",
        "additional_details": "We were told that after Brexit there would be more opportunity for food labelling, and that the government was considering this. (1) Nothing of any substance has happened! The government has not lived up to its words. Defra figures show that in one week in March 2022 more than half of all non-stunned, kosher-slaughtered cattle was rejected by Jewish authorities and sold to the wider public instead. (2) I would remind the government an election is coming!\r\n(1) https://petition.parliament.uk/archived/petitions/229231  \r\n(2) https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/1096782/Results-of-the-2022-FSA-Slaughter-Sector-Survey-in-England-and-Wales.pdf \r\n",
        "background": "Some \u2013 including members of some other religions \u2013 may not wish to consume any halal or kosher-certified item. We are asking for mandatory prominent labelling to make an informed choice. ",
